  "time_ut": 1662378893,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d9c\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dba\u0dd2\u0dc6\u0ddc\u0dc3\u0dda\u0da7\u0dca \u0d86\u0db1\u0dba\u0db1\u0dba\u0da7 \u0d85\u0dc0\u0dc3\u0dbb \u0daf\u0dd9\u0db1 \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0dc3\u0da7\u0dca \u0db4\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dba \u0dc4\u0dd9\u0da7 \u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dda\u0db1\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Gazette to allow import of glyphosate to Parliament tomorrow",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The gazette with regulations under the Import and Export (Control) Act permitting the import of glyphosate will be submitted to Parliament tomorrow (6).",
        "The Government Finance Committee has approved the gazette with regulations under the Import and Export (Control) Act allowing the import of glyphosate.",
        "The Government's Finance Committee recently considered the regulations enacted under the Import and Export (Control) Act No. 1 of 1969 regarding the permission to import glyphosate, which is used as a weed killer in the plantation sector, and after a long discussion, the committee approved it.",
        "The Parliamentary Committee on Government Finance met last (02) under the chairmanship of its Chairman, Member of Parliament (Dr.) Harsha De Silva.",
        "According to this gazette, import licenses for glyphosate will be issued subject to the recommendation of the pesticide registrar.",
        "Although the Government's Finance Committee has approved these regulations, the Chairman of the Committee has stated that the approval is subject to conditions.",
        "Mr. Harsha de Silva pointed out that further decisions should be taken after holding a wide discussion about the prepared report on the use of glyphosate in Sri Lanka's plantation crops.",
        "Minister Vidura Wickramanaya, MPs Wijitha Herath, Shehan Semasinghe, Pramitha Bandara Thennakone, Dr. Suren Raghavan, MA Sumanthiran, Harshana Rajakaruna, Chaminda Wijesiri, Anupa Pascual and Professor Ranjith Bandara participated in this discussion.",
        "Also, the officials of the Ministry of Finance, Import and Export Control Department, Ministry of Plantation Industry, Ministry of Agriculture and Pesticides Registry Office also participated in this meeting and the officials representing the Ministry of Health connected through online technology."
      ],
